      "solution": "<p>The rate of nucleophilic addition decreased due to steric crowding around carbonyl carbon \\&amp; increased by electron withdrawing group if the steric crowding is same hence the reactivity towards nucleophilic addition will be</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m7d7ff88/d5f0c618-2b42-4fe4-9123-eaed8cbd0f47/287f8580-ef76-11ef-81e6-6774abfb9501/file-jaoe38c1m7d7ff89.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m7d7ff88/d5f0c618-2b42-4fe4-9123-eaed8cbd0f47/287f8580-ef76-11ef-81e6-6774abfb9501/file-jaoe38c1m7d7ff89.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2025 (Online) 24th January Morning Shift Chemistry - Aldehydes, Ketones and Carboxylic Acids Question 52 English Explanation\"></p>",
